This pattern uses `\\w+script` — which matches any word characters followed by "script". This means it would match `javascript:` but NOT patterns like `vbscript:` since "vbscript" ends in "script". Wait, let me reconsider: `\\w+script` means one or more word chars THEN "script" — so "javascript" → "java" + "script" would match. Let me check edge cases.

The pattern `^(?:\\w+script|data):` — looking at this:
- `javascript:` → matches `\\w+script` (java + script) ✓ blocked
- `vbscript:` → matches `\\w+script` (vb + script) ✓ blocked  
- `data:` → matches `data` ✓ blocked
- But what about `JAVASCRIPT:` → CASE_INSENSITIVE is set ✓ blocked

